Function Reference/spawn cron « WordPress Codex
-----------

Send request to run cron through HTTP request that doesn't halt page
loading. Will not run more than once every 60 seconds.

Usage
-----

` <?php spawn_cron( $local_time ); ?> `

Parameters
----------

Return Values
-------------

 (null) 
:   Cron could not be spawned, because it is not needed to run.

Examples
--------

Notes
-----

-   Cron is named after a unix program which runs unattended scheduled
    tasks.

Change Log
----------

Since: 2.1.0

Source File
-----------

`spawn_cron()` is located in `wp-includes/cron.php`.

